    public class LeapHelperImpl
extends java.lang.Object

      • LeapHelperImpl

        public LeapHelperImpl(java.lang.String hostname,
                      boolean ignoreSSL,
                      java.lang.String protocol,
                      java.lang.String username,
                      char[] password,
                      java.lang.String freedomIdentifyKey)
               throws LeapHelperException
        Parameters:
        hostname - - The server host (i.e. "https://myformsserver.com")
        context - - The context of the forms application (i.e. "forms-basic")
        ignoreSSL - - A development flag to bypass certificate verification. Defaults to false. Should not be true in a production implementation.
        protocol - - If ignoreSSL is "true" then you must specify a communication protocol, i.e. SSL, TLSv1.2
        username - - The username to use for this API request
        password - - The user's password
        freedomIdentifyKey - - The value to assign as the freedomIdentifyKey
        Throws:
        LeapHelperException - if hostname is not specified
        LeapHelperException - if username is not specified
        LeapHelperException - if password is not specified
